      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "LADY BLAZINGTON (8) rocketed out of the boxes with a strong early sectional but gathered in and finished in the minors when second (17.19) at this track over 300m. Can go on with it. REEL 'EM MINI (7) goes very well at the course and distance with five wins and a placing from 12 starts. Was out of the placings last time (20.54) at Grafton in a Free For All, finishing seventh and beaten 9 lengths. Looks suited here and can measure up. MARTINIQUE (2) had the drop on the lead early on but could only manage second, beaten 1.3 lengths (17.07) at this track in a Grade 5 over 300m. Yet to win out of this box but has been in the placings four times from six starts. Expected to be in this for a long way. ROUND 'EM UP (1) was in the money last start and poses a threat again.",
